## Limitations

The findings are limited by the availability of recent and comprehensive data on paraphilias, particularly regarding female paraphilias, which are less studied. Additionally, cultural biases in reporting and diagnosing paraphilias may skew the perceived prevalence among genders. Further research is needed to explore these aspects in diverse cultural contexts.

